Program: Last Word
Title: A president, a jazz trumpeter, an economist, a socialite and codebreaker and a conductor
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b01r14tb
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 10 Mar 2013
On Last Word this week: Jazzman Kenny Ball, remembered by bandmate John Bennet. Government minister Oliver Letwin tells us about the work of his American-born father, the economist William Letwin. Sarah Baring, who combined a debutante high-life with code-breaking at Bletchley Park during the war. German conductor Wolfgang Sawallisch. And as President Hugo Chavez lies is state, we hear from Venezuela about the life of the charismatic and controversial politician. Show less